de.timoh.JStormLib

Interface StormLibWin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.sun.jna.AltCallingConvention, com.sun.jna.Library, com.sun.jna.win32.StdCall, com.sun.jna.win32.StdCallLibrary

    public interface StormLibWin
extends com.sun.jna.win32.StdCallLibrary
    StormLibWin is used to open and manipulate MPQ-Archives from JAVA on Windows-Systems.

    This interface is compatible with x86 and x64 systems if both DLLs are present. (StormLib_x86.dll and StormLib_x64.dll). By default the path to the DLLs is System.getProperty("user.dir").

    This Interface is a wrapper for the StormLib.dll developed by Ladislav Zezula for Windows.

      • SFileOpenArchive

        byte SFileOpenArchive(java.lang.String szMpqName,
                    int dwPriority,
                    int dwFlags,
                    com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLEByReference phMpq)
        Opens a MPQ archive. During the open operation, the archive is checked for corruptions, internal (listfile) and (attributes) are loaded, unless specified otherwise. The archive is open for read and write operations, unless MPQ_OPEN_READ_ONLY is specified. Note that StormLib maintains list of all files within the MPQ, as long as the MPQ is open. At the moment of MPQ opening, when the MPQ contains an internal list file, that listfile is parsed and all files in the listfile are checked against the hash table. Every file name that exists within the MPQ is added to the internal name list. The name list can be fuhrter extended by calling SFileAddListFile(com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLE, java.lang.String).
        Parameters:
        szMpqName - Archive file name to open
        dwPriority - Priority of the archive for later search. StormLib does not use this parameter, set it to zero.
        dwFlags - Flags that specify additional options about how to open the file.
        phMpq - Pointer to a variable of HANDLE type, where the opened archive handle will be stored
        Returns:
        When the function succeeds, it returns nonzero and phMPQ contains the handle of the opened archive. When the archive cannot be open, function returns false and Kernel32.GetLastError() gives the error code.
        See Also:
        http://www.zezula.net/en/mpq/stormlib/sfileopenarchive.html

      • SFileCreateArchive

        byte SFileCreateArchive(java.lang.String szMpqName,
                      int dwFlags,
                      int dwMaxFileCount,
                      com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLEByReference phMpq)
        Opens or creates the MPQ archive. The function can also convert an existing file to MPQ archive. The MPQ archive is always open for write operations. The function internally verifies the file using SFileOpenArchive(java.lang.String, int, int, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLEByReference). If the file already exists and it is an MPQ archive, the function fails and Kernel32.GetLastError() returns ERROR_ALREADY_EXISTS.
        Parameters:
        szMpqName - Archive file name to be created
        dwFlags - Specifies additional flags for MPQ creation process
        dwMaxFileCount - File count limit. Must be in range of HASH_TABLE_SIZE_MIN (0x04) and HASH_TABLE_SIZE_MAX (0x80000)
        phMpq - Pointer to a variable of HANDLE type, where the opened archive handle will be stored.
        Returns:
        When the function succeeds, it returns nonzero and phMPQ contains the handle of the new archive. On an error, the function returns false and Kernel32.GetLastError() gives the error code.
        See Also:
        http://www.zezula.net/en/mpq/stormlib/sfilecreatearchive.html

      • SFileFlushArchive

        byte SFileFlushArchive(com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLE hMpq)
        Saves any in-memory structures to the MPQ archive on disk. Due to performance reasons, StormLib caches several data structures in memory (e.g. block table or hash table). When a file is added to the MPQ, those structures are only updated in memory. Calling SFileFlushArchive forces saving in-memory MPQ tables to the file, preventing a MPQ corruption incase of power down or crash of the calling application. Note that this function is called internally when the archive is closed.
        Parameters:
        hMpq - Handle to an open MPQ.
        Returns:
        When the function succeeds, it returns nonzero. On an error, the function returns false and Kernel32.GetLastError() gives the error code.
        See Also:
        http://www.zezula.net/en/mpq/stormlib/sfileflusharchive.html

      • SFileAddListFile

        int SFileAddListFile(com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLE hMpq,
                   java.lang.String szListFile)
        StormLib maintains list of all files within the MPQ, as long as the MPQ is open. At the moment of MPQ opening, when the MPQ contains an internal list file, that listfile is parsed and all files in the listfile are checked against the hash table. Every file name that exists within the MPQ is added to the internal name list. This is done by calling SFileAddListFile internally. SFileAddListFile adds an external listfile to the open MPQ. Note that the listfile is merely added to the memory structures of the open MPQ. On-disk structures of the MPQ are not changed. Use this function to specify an extra listfile to an opened MPQ, for example when there is no internal listfile, or if the internal listfile is not complete.
        Parameters:
        hMpq - Handle to an open MPQ.
        szListFile - Listfile name to add. If this parameter is NULL, the function adds the internal listfile from the MPQ, if present. Adding the same listfile multiple times has no effect.
        Returns:
        When the function succeeds, it returns ERROR_SUCCESS. On an error, the function returns error code.
        See Also:
        http://www.zezula.net/en/mpq/stormlib/sfileaddlistfile.html

                       java.lang.String szListFile,
                       byte bReserved)
        Performs a complete archive rebuild, effectively defragmenting the MPQ archive, removing all gaps that have been created by adding, replacing, renaming or deleting files within the archive. SFileCompactArchive might take several minutes to complete, depending on size of the archive being rebuilt.         szListFile - Allows to specify an additional listfile, that will be used together with internal listfile. Can be null.
        bReserved - Not used, set to zero.
        Returns:
        When the function succeeds, it returns nonzero. On an error, the function returns false and Kernel32.GetLastError() gives the error code.
        See Also:
        http://www.zezula.net/en/mpq/stormlib/sfilecompactarchive.html

                   java.lang.String szFileName,
                   int dwSearchScope)
        Removes a file from MPQ. The MPQ must have been open by SFileOpenArchive(java.lang.String, int, int, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLEByReference) or created by SFileCreateArchive(java.lang.String, int, int, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLEByReference). Note that this operation leaves a gap in the MPQ file. To reduce size of the MPQ, use SFileCompactArchive(com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLE, java.lang.String, byte).
        Parameters:
        hMpq - Handle to an open MPQ. This handle must have been obtained by calling SFileOpenArchive(java.lang.String, int, int, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLEByReference) or SFileCreateArchive(java.lang.String, int, int, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinNT.HANDLEByReference).
        szFileName - Name of a file to be removed.
        dwSearchScope - This parameter is ignored in the current version of StormLib.
        Returns:
        When the function succeeds, it returns nonzero. On an error, the function returns 0 and Kernel32.GetLastError() gives the error code.
        See Also:
        http://www.zezula.net/en/mpq/stormlib/sfileremovefile.html
